HEADWORD: Thomson process
<hw>Thomson process</hw>. <ety>[After Elihu <etsep>Thomson</etsep>,
American inventor.]</ety> <def>A process of electric welding in which
heat is developed by a large current passing through the
metal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

